The paper discusses the implementation of a spatial channel model for wireless networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure (NI) and information theory (IT). The use of millimeter waves also suggests a potential connection to multimedia (MM) and systems and control (SY). Additionally, the paper mentions the integration of the model into ns-3, a network simulator, which could be relevant to the area of architecture (AR).
